		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Ann Nietzke</strong></span> has worked since 1986 in a Los Angeles psychiatric shelter for homeless people. Her novel <em>Windowlight</em> won the Los Angeles P.E.N. Award for best first fiction, and her work has appeared in <em>Shenandoah, </em>the<em> Village Voice, Playgirl,</em> and elsewhere.</p><a href="/contributors/ann-nietzke" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
