			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="3121">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>In an era of hesitation, Ann Nietzke chose to act [&ldquo;<a href="/article/1343">Natalie</a>,&rdquo; August 1993]. Her profound compassion for Natalie and the courage it took to act upon that compassion make her a role model for us all.</p>

<p>I am so afraid that the nineties will go down in history as the decade when morally strong people &mdash; who <em>knew</em> what should be done &mdash; were paralyzed into inaction by the dark concept of &ldquo;political correctness,&rdquo; that phrase used by sneering cynics to describe any act of simple concern and kindness.</p>

<p>Thank you for printing Nietzke&rsquo;s essay. I feel cleaner, too.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Robin Parks<br>Long Beach, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
